    • Method Detail

      • httpMethod

        public static Storage.SignUrlOption httpMethod(HttpMethod httpMethod)
        The HTTP method to be used with the signed URL. If this method is not called, defaults to GET.

      • withContentType

        public static Storage.SignUrlOption withContentType()
        Use it if signature should include the blob's content-type. When used, users of the signed URL should include the blob's content-type with their request. If using this URL from a browser, you must include a content type that matches what the browser will send.

      • withMd5

        public static Storage.SignUrlOption withMd5()
        Use it if signature should include the blob's md5. When used, users of the signed URL should include the blob's md5 with their request.

      • withExtHeaders

        public static Storage.SignUrlOption withExtHeaders(Map<String,String> extHeaders)
        Use it if signature should include the blob's canonicalized extended headers. When used, users of the signed URL should include the canonicalized extended headers with their request.
        See Also:

      • signWith

        public static Storage.SignUrlOption signWith(com.google.auth.ServiceAccountSigner signer)
        Provides a service account signer to sign the URL. If not provided an attempt will be made to get it from the environment.
        See Also:
        Service account

      • withHostName

        public static Storage.SignUrlOption withHostName(String hostName)
        Use a different host name than the default host name 'storage.googleapis.com'
